io.permazen.core.type

Class FloatArrayType

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.permazen.core.FieldType<T>
      • io.permazen.core.type.NonNullFieldType<T>
        • io.permazen.core.type.ArrayType<T,E>
          • io.permazen.core.type.Base64ArrayType<float[],Float>
            • io.permazen.core.type.FloatArrayType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparator<float[]>

    public class FloatArrayType
extends Base64ArrayType<float[],Float>
    float[] array type. Does not support null arrays.

    Array elements are encoded using FloatType, and the array is terminated by 0x00000000, which is an encoded value that can never be emitted by FloatType.

      • hasPrefix0xff

        public boolean hasPrefix0xff()
        Description copied from class: FieldType
        Determine whether any of this field type's encoded values start with a 0xff byte. Certain optimizations are possible when this is not the case. It is safe for this method to always return true.

        Note: changing the return value of this method usually means changing the binary encoding, resulting in an incompatible type.

        The implementation in FieldType returns true.

        Overrides:
        hasPrefix0xff in class FieldType<float[]>
        Returns:
        true if an encoded value starting with 0xff exists
